originalText.text: I’ve run into issues with the Jitney in the summer, but the rides to EQ in the off season have been wonderful and very reasonably priced. 96th & 3rd Ave. to New Moon Cafe for $31. Not bad!

originalText.text: I used to ride the Hampton Jitney from 92 to 05 to go to the Southampton Fresh Air Home between a week and 3 weeks. Never had a problem. This must be a stop for all other services,cause I use to get picked up and dropped off at the Hospital For Special Surgery.

originalText.text: We use the stop on Lexington Avenue between 59th and 60th Street. Works perfectly as the street is wide and busses have the full block. It's the only way we would ever go to Southampton. We prefer the Ambassador and for a few extra dollars reserve a seat.
